    },
    "aximar": {}
  },
  "cells": [
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": "# Least Squares Curve Fitting\n\nThis notebook demonstrates **polynomial curve fitting** via least squares,\nhighlighting the **symbolic-numeric bridge**: we build design matrices\nnumerically with `ndarray` operations, solve the least-squares problem with\n`np_lstsq` (wrapping LAPACK's SVD), and then reconstruct the fitted polynomial\nas a symbolic Maxima expression for plotting and analysis.\n\nKey functions: `np_linspace`, `np_lstsq`, `np_hstack`, `np_reshape`, `np_matmul`, `np_pow`.",
      "metadata": {}
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": "load(\"numerics\")$\nload(\"ax-plots\")$",
      "metadata": {},
      "execution_count": 113,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": "## Generating Noisy Data\n\nWe start from a known quadratic function $f(x) = 0.5 x^2 - 2x + 1$ and\nadd Gaussian noise. This gives us a ground truth to compare against.",
      "metadata": {}
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": "/* True function: f(x) = 0.5*x^2 - 2*x + 1 */\nn : 20$\nx : np_linspace(0, 5, n)$\n\n/* Evaluate f at each x and add noise */\ny : np_add(\n  np_add(\n    np_scale(0.5, np_pow(x, 2)),\n    np_scale(-2.0, x)\n  ),\n  np_add(\n    ndarray(makelist(1.0, i, 1, n)),\n    np_scale(0.3, np_randn([n]))\n  )\n)$\n\nprint(\"x (first 5):\", makelist(np_ref(x, i), i, 0, 4))$\nprint(\"y (first 5):\", makelist(np_ref(y, i), i, 0, 4))$",
      "metadata": {},
      "execution_count": 114,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "name": "stdout",
          "output_type": "stream",
          "text": [
            "x (first 5):\n            [0.0,0.2631578947368421,0.5263157894736842,0.7894736842105263,\n             1.0526315789473684]\ny (first 5):\n            [1.144367961890701,0.3465674007798698,-0.1013859777412156,\n             -0.2302246196332074,-0.6000505351780027]"
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": "/* Plot the noisy data */\nax_draw2d(\n  color=red, marker_size=6,\n  name=\"Noisy data\",\n  points(np_to_list(x), np_to_list(y)),\n  color=black, dash=\"dash\", name=\"True: 0.5x^2 - 2x + 1\",\n  explicit(0.5*t^2 - 2*t + 1, t, 0, 5),\n  title=\"Noisy Observations from a Quadratic\",\n  xlabel=\"x\", ylabel=\"y\",\n  grid=true\n)$",
      "metadata": {},
      "execution_count": 115,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "data": {
