    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": "## The Vandermonde Matrix [S+N]\n\nTo fit a degree-$d$ polynomial $p(x) = a_0 + a_1 x + a_2 x^2 + \\cdots + a_d x^d$\nto data $(x_i, y_i)$, we form the **Vandermonde matrix** (or design matrix) $V$\nwith entries $V_{ij} = x_i^{\\,j}$:\n\n$$\nV = \\begin{pmatrix}\n  1 & x_1 & x_1^2 & \\cdots & x_1^d \\\\\n  1 & x_2 & x_2^2 & \\cdots & x_2^d \\\\\n  \\vdots & \\vdots & \\vdots & \\ddots & \\vdots \\\\\n  1 & x_m & x_m^2 & \\cdots & x_m^d\n\\end{pmatrix}\n$$\n\nThe least-squares fit then solves $V \\mathbf{a} \\approx \\mathbf{y}$ for the\ncoefficient vector $\\mathbf{a} = (a_0, a_1, \\ldots, a_d)^T$.\n\nWe can inspect the symbolic structure first, then build it numerically.",
      "metadata": {}
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": "/* Symbolic Vandermonde structure for degree 2 */\nprint(\"Symbolic Vandermonde (degree 2) for points x1..x4:\")$\ngenmatrix(lambda([i, j], x[i]^(j-1)), 4, 3);",
      "metadata": {},
      "execution_count": 116,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "name": "stdout",
          "output_type": "stream",
          "text": [
            "Symbolic Vandermonde (degree 2) for points x1..x4:"
          ]
        },
        {
          "data": {
            "text/latex": [
              "\\ifx\\endpmatrix\\undefined\\pmatrix{\\else\\begin{pmatrix}\\fi 1&\\left(\\text{ndarray}((20), DOUBLE-FLOAT)\\right)_{1}&\\left(\\text{ndarray}((20), DOUBLE-FLOAT)\\right)_{1}^2\\cr 1&\\left(\\text{ndarray}((20), DOUBLE-FLOAT)\\right)_{2}&\\left(\\text{ndarray}((20), DOUBLE-FLOAT)\\right)_{2}^2\\cr 1&\\left(\\text{ndarray}((20), DOUBLE-FLOAT)\\right)_{3}&\\left(\\text{ndarray}((20), DOUBLE-FLOAT)\\right)_{3}^2\\cr 1&\\left(\\text{ndarray}((20), DOUBLE-FLOAT)\\right)_{4}&\\left(\\text{ndarray}((20), DOUBLE-FLOAT)\\right)_{4}^2\\cr\\ifx\\endpmatrix\\undefined}\\else\\end{pmatrix}\\fi "
            ]
          },
          "execution_count": 116,
          "metadata": {},
          "output_type": "execute_result"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": "/* Build the Vandermonde matrix numerically for degree 2 */\n/* Each column is x^j for j = 0, 1, 2 */\nvander(xv, deg) := block([cols],\n  cols : np_reshape(np_ones([np_size(xv)]), [np_size(xv), 1]),\n  for j : 1 thru deg do\n    cols : np_hstack(cols, np_reshape(np_pow(xv, j), [np_size(xv), 1])),\n  cols\n)$\n\nV : vander(x, 2)$\nprint(\"Vandermonde shape:\", np_shape(V))$\nprint(\"First 3 rows:\")$\nfor i : 0 thru 2 do\n  print(\"  \", np_to_list(np_row(V, i)))$",
      "metadata": {},
      "execution_count": 117,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "name": "stdout",
          "output_type": "stream",
          "text": [
            "Vandermonde shape: [20,3]\nFirst 3 rows:\n   [1.0,0.0,0.0]\n   [1.0,0.2631578947368421,0.06925207756232686]\n   [1.0,0.5263157894736842,0.27700831024930744]"
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": "## Solving with np_lstsq\n\nThe function `np_lstsq(A, b)` minimises $\\|A x - b\\|_2$ using SVD.\nIt returns `[x, residuals, rank, singular_values]`.",
      "metadata": {}
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": "/* Solve the least-squares problem V * a = y */\ny_col : np_reshape(y, [n, 1])$\n[coeffs_nd, residuals, rank_V, sv] : np_lstsq(V, y_col)$\n\ncoeffs_list : np_to_list(coeffs_nd)$\na0 : coeffs_list[1]$\na1 : coeffs_list[2]$\na2 : coeffs_list[3]$\n\nprint(\"Fitted coefficients:\")$\nprint(\"  a0 =\", a0, \"  (true: 1.0)\")$\nprint(\"  a1 =\", a1, \"  (true: -2.0)\")$\nprint(\"  a2 =\", a2, \"  (true: 0.5)\")$\nprint(\"  rank =\", rank_V)$\n\n/* Reconstruct the fitted polynomial symbolically */\np_fit : a0 + a1*t + a2*t^2;\nprint(\"Fitted polynomial: p(t) =\", p_fit)$",
      "metadata": {},
      "execution_count": 118,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "name": "stdout",
          "output_type": "stream",
          "text": [
            "Fitted coefficients:\n  a0 = 1.0837053490879573   (true: 1.0)\n  a1 = -2.1517272135665984   (true: -2.0)\n  a2 = 0.5273594310358118   (true: 0.5)\n  rank = 3\n0.5273594310358118*t^2-2.1517272135665984*t+1.0837053490879573\nFitted polynomial: p(t) =\n                         0.5273594310358118*t^2-2.1517272135665984*t\n                                               +1.0837053490879573"
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": "## Plotting the Fit\n\nWe overlay the fitted curve (a symbolic expression) onto the noisy data.",
      "metadata": {}
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": "ax_draw2d(\n  color=red, marker_size=6,\n  name=\"Data\",\n  points(np_to_list(x), np_to_list(y)),\n  color=blue, line_width=2, name=\"Least-squares fit (deg 2)\",\n  explicit(p_fit, t, 0, 5),\n  color=black, dash=\"dash\", name=\"True curve\",\n  explicit(0.5*t^2 - 2*t + 1, t, 0, 5),\n  title=\"Quadratic Least-Squares Fit\",\n  xlabel=\"x\", ylabel=\"y\",\n  grid=true\n)$",
      "metadata": {},
      "execution_count": 119,
